      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/Tournaments_and_Matches\" title=\"Tournaments and Matches\">Tournaments</a> * <a href=\"/ACM_North_American_Computer_Chess_Championship\" title=\"ACM North American Computer Chess Championship\">ACM North American Computer Chess Championship</a> * ACM 1978</b>\n</p><p><b><a href=\"/ACM_1977\" title=\"ACM 1977\">&lt; Prev</a> <a href=\"/ACM_1979\" title=\"ACM 1979\">Next &gt;</a></b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/File:Marriott_Wardman_Park_by_Matthew_Bisanz.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/52/Marriott_Wardman_Park_by_Matthew_Bisanz.jpg/330px-Marriott_Wardman_Park_by_Matthew_Bisanz.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"152\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/52/Marriott_Wardman_Park_by_Matthew_Bisanz.jpg/500px-Marriott_Wardman_Park_by_Matthew_Bisanz.jpg 1.5x, https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/52/Marriott_Wardman_Park_by_Matthew_Bisanz.jpg/960px-Marriott_Wardman_Park_by_Matthew_Bisanz.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:Marriott_Wardman_Park_by_Matthew_Bisanz.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Sheraton Park Hotel <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p>The <a href=\"/ACM\" title=\"ACM\">ACM's</a> <b>Ninth North American Computer Chess Championship</b> (NACCC) was held from December 4 to 6, <a href=\"/Timeline#1978\" title=\"Timeline\">1978</a> at the <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marriott_Wardman_Park\">Sheraton Park Hotel</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Washington%2C_D.C.\">Washington, D.C.</a>, USA.\n</p><p>Several <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Celebrity\">celebrities</a> from the world of chess and from the computing field were attending the ACM 1978 computer chess tournament, notably <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edward_Lasker\">Edward Lasker</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Byrne_%28chess_player%29\">Robert Byrne</a>, and <a href=\"/ACM\" title=\"ACM\">ACM</a> president <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daniel_D._McCracken\">Daniel D. McCracken</a>, who presented trophies to the three prizewinners. Two remarkable incidents appeared in two games of the new American Champion <a href=\"/Belle\" title=\"Belle\">Belle</a> - in <a href=\"/ACM_1978#R2\" title=\"ACM 1978\">round 2</a> versus <a href=\"/Chess_(Program)\" title=\"Chess (Program)\">Chess 4.7</a>, when Chess missed the win with 21... Nxd3, and in <a href=\"/Belle#Blitz\" title=\"Belle\">round 4</a> versus <a href=\"/Blitz\" title=\"Blitz\">Blitz 6.5</a>, which according to <a href=\"/David_Levy\" title=\"David Levy\">David Levy</a> produced the most beautiful combination ever played by a computer program so far <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> . \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Final_Standing\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Final Standing</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Participants\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Participants</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Photos\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Photos</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Selected_Games\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected Games</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Further_Games\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Further Games</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Louis_Kessler\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Louis Kessler</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Spracklens\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Spracklens</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Reports\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Reports</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">8</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">9</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Final_Standing\">Final Standing</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=ACM_1978&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Final Standing\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n\n<tr>\n<th> #\n</th>\n<th> Program\n</th>\n<th> CC\n</th>\n<th> 1\n</th>\n<th> 2\n</th>\n<th> 3\n</th>\n<th> 4\n</th>\n<th> P\n</th>\n<th> SOS\n</th>\n<th> SoDOS\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<th> 1\n</th>\n<td>  <a href=\"/Belle\" title=\"Belle\">Belle</a>\n</td>\n<th> US\n</th>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\"> 8b1\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\"> <a href=\"/ACM_1978#R2\" title=\"ACM 